Title: Financial Markets and Economic Growth in Poland: Simulations with an Econometric Model
Abstract: In this paper we present simulations of economic performance of the Polish economy based on a quarterly econometric model. The model consists of 22 stochastic equations which link the financial market with the real economy. The purpose of the research is to present effects o f changes to domestic and foreign interest rates and the EUR/USD exchange rate on economic growth in Poland over the period Q2, 1993 - Q2, 2003.
